  "text": "CACNA1c (LQT8) -Timothy syndrome LQT8 is a rare variant of LQTS characterized by marked QT interval prolongation, often presenting with 2:1 functional atrioventricular block and macroscopic T wave alternans, and syndactyly. LQT8 is highly malignant, and 10/17 (59%) of the children reported by Splawski et al. [CITATION_1] died at a mean age of 2.5 years. Some children with Timothy syndrome also had congenital heart diseases, immune deficiency, intermittent hypoglycemia, cognitive abnormalities, and autism.",
